collections.name: MIND
collections.description:
As we careen toward a technological chasm, the very essence of what it means to be human rises in stark relief. No longer can we afford to glide forward on autopilot, lulled by the hum of machines and the promises of algorithms. We stand at a precipice—between the messy specter of consciousness and the cold precision of machines—where human intelligence, machine learning, and state architectures converge in an inevitable reckoning.
In this liminal space, the Mind NFT is born. Not simply as a digital artifact, but as a living inquiry—an unfolding, a mirror, a call. The project arises from a need both urgent and poetic: to ask again, and more deeply, Who are we? Where is our mind? What is normal, and what is divergent
The Mind NFT explores the rift between synthetic logic and sentient chaos, between Large Language Models and the language of the heart, yes the toroidal heart. Between artificial and “authentic” authored by us, through us, with us, by us. Therein lies another truth still.

collections.name: Queen Marrow
collections.description:

The stark contrast of black and white in this piece serves as a visual representation of duality—the balance between light and darkness, strength and fragility. The black symbolizes the depth of the unknown, the strength found in darkness, and the quiet power that resides within. The white contrasts this, representing purity, clarity, and the sustaining force of life that contrasts yet complements the darker elements.

The marrow in the bone, as the central focus of the piece, symbolizes the core of existence and vitality. Just as bone provides structure, marrow is the source of life, creating blood that sustains the body.
